Sanders [defends Snowden](http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/01/06/snowden-clemency-sanders-nsa/4344467/), [opposed the Freedom Act](http://www.boston.com/news/politics/2015/06/01/bernie-sanders-and-rand-paul-agree-the-nsa-goes-too-far/RB84u3L4NFzvmF9shCGszO/story.html), [opposed CISA](http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/27/cisa-cybersecurity-bill-senate-vote), [supports legalizing marijuana](https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/sanders-will-propose-nixing-marijuana-from-federal-list-of-dangerous-drugs/2015/10/28/be8c3adc-7da2-11e5-b575-d8dcfedb4ea1_story.html), [opposed the war in Iraq, and opposed the Patriot Act](http://www.politifact.com/punditfact/article/2015/sep/02/11-examples-hillary-clinton-and-bernie-sanders-hol/). It's easy to criticize him, but it's also easy to find ways in which he fights federal overreach.
